    "recap_url": "https://www.utrockets.com/news/2026/3/22/baseball-rockets-rally-to-tie-in-ninth-but-walkoff-drops-toledo-in-extras-6-5",
    "recap_headline": "University of Toledo",
    "recap_text": "MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. \u2013 The Toledo baseball team got a two-run home run to tie the game in the ninth inning, but Central Michigan pushed across the winning run in the 11th in a 6-5 final at Keilitz Field on Sunday.\nThe Rockets (10-11, 6-3 MAC) took the early 2-0 lead and led 3-2 going into the seventh. The Chippewas (9-11, 3-6 MAC) scored once in the seventh and took the lead with two runs in the eighth.\nCharlie Scholvin\ntied the game with two outs in the ninth with a home run. After a scoreless 10th and top of the 11th, CMU delivered the game-winning RBI single with two outs. The Chippewas took 2-of-3 games in the weekend set.\nToledo's offense got multi-hit bids from\nTroy Sudbrook\n,\nSaborn Campbell\nand\nLuke Walton\n. Scholvin's tying home run was his first of the season. Sudbrook tied his season high with three hits and was a home run from hitting for the cycle. He has seven multi-hit games in his last eight appearances.\nFreshman\nHayden Frey\npitched seven solid innings in his second start of the season, allowing three runs on seven hits and striking out nine batters.\nMichael Fliss\n(0-1) pitched the final 3.2 innings, and forced extras with scoreless ninth and 10th innings, but took the loss with the 11th-inning run.\nQuoting Head Coach\nRob Reinstetle\n\"Always hurts to lose being walked off in extra innings. We had some really bad luck today. We had a guy trip on bases and not score, a collision and dropped ball allowing runs, and a ball by Sudbrook that was one inch from being the game-winning home run. But we had some bright spots. I thought\nHayden Frey\nand\nMichael Fliss\nboth threw the ball really well. I also liked our fight after giving up two runs in the bottom of the eighth. We didn't quit and Chuck Scholvin tied it up with a big two-run homer in the ninth. We are still 6-3 in MAC play and right in the hunt at the top. We have to wipe that one away and get ready for a big week of baseball.\"\nTop Rocket Hitters\nTroy Sudbrook\n\u2013 3-for-5, 1 RBI, 2 runs, 1 2B, 1 3B\nLuke Walton\n\u2013 2-for-4, 1 RBI,\nSaborn Campbell\n\u2013 2-for-5, 1 run, 1 2B\nCharlie Scholvin\n\u2013 1-for-5, HR (1), 2 RBIs, 1 run\nPitching Lines\nHayden Frey\n\u2013 7.0 IP, 7 H, 3 R, 3 ER, 2 BB, 9 Ks\nMichael Fliss\n(L, 0-1) \u2013 3.2 IP, 5 H, 3 R, 3 ER, 1 BB, 3 Ks\nHow it Happened\nHayden Frey\nstranded two runners in each of the first two innings to keep the game scoreless.\nTroy Sudbrook's\nRBI double and\nLuke Walton's\nRBI single put Toledo in front, 2-0 in the third.\nLogan Keilen's two run home run tied the game in the bottom of the third.\nToledo reclaimed the lead in the fifth, 3-2, on an\nAlex McCranie\nsacrifice fly.\nThe Chippewas put runners on first-and-third in the seventh, setting up the tying run on a fielder's choice.\nA misplayed fly ball resulted in a two-run double for a 5-3 Central Michigan lead in the eighth.\nWith Toledo down to its last out,\nCharlie Scholvin\ndelivered a two-run home run on the first pitch to tie the game 5-5. Sudbrook nearly hit the go-ahead home run in the next at bat, but the ball hit the top of the wall.\nCentral Michigan put a runner on second with two outs in the 11th, before Harrison Bowman's single plated the winning run.\nUp Next\nToledo has midweek games at Butler on Tuesday, March 24 and at Michigan on Wednesday, March 25, followed by a weekend MAC series at Akron on March 27-29. Tuesday's first pitch at Butler is at 4:00 p.m.",
